## React Query (TanStack Query)

### Quando usar

- Dados do Supabase (patients, cases, case_messages, authenticated_users).
- Cache, refetch, invalidation e loading/error states centralizados.

### ConfiguraÃ§Ã£o

- `QueryClientProvider` no layout raiz (ou `(dashboard)`).
- Preferir `@tanstack/react-query` (v5).

### Query Keys

Estrutura consistente e hierÃ¡rquica para invalidation.

```ts
// lib/query-keys.ts
export const queryKeys = {
  patients: {
    all: ['patients'] as const,
    lists: () => [...queryKeys.patients.all, 'list'] as const,
    list: (userPhone: string, search?: string) =>
      [...queryKeys.patients.lists(), userPhone, search ?? ''] as const,
    details: () => [...queryKeys.patients.all, 'detail'] as const,
    detail: (id: string) => [...queryKeys.patients.details(), id] as const,
  },
  cases: {
    all: ['cases'] as const,
    lists: () => [...queryKeys.cases.all, 'list'] as const,
    list: (userPhone: string, status?: 'active' | 'closed') =>
      [...queryKeys.cases.lists(), userPhone, status ?? 'all'] as const,
    detail: (id: string) => [...queryKeys.cases.all, 'detail', id] as const,
  },
};
```

### useQuery

- Chamar funÃ§Ãµes dos `modules/` dentro da query fn.
- `queryKey` do `queryKeys`.
- `enabled` quando depender de `userPhone` ou outro dado.

```tsx
const { data, isLoading, error } = useQuery({
  queryKey: queryKeys.patients.list(userPhone, search),
  queryFn: () => getPatientsByUserPhone(supabase, userPhone),
  enabled: !!userPhone,
});
```

